62
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:44,660
But if we forget about that redshift

63
00:02:44,660 --> 00:02:50,200
and we just fold in the redshift into our calculations,

64
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:54,320
and ask how hot the universe was at various places,

65
00:02:54,540 --> 00:03:00,280
then there's some place where it becomes as hot,

66
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:02,200
just about as hot as the surface of the sun.

67
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:05,780
That's the place where the universe became opaque.

68
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:11,540
It became opaque because the atoms,

69
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,920
particularly the hydrogen atoms,

70
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:16,120
the universe was mainly made out of hydrogen

71
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:18,260
and a bit of helium.

72
00:03:19,740 --> 00:03:20,700
The hydrogen atoms,

73
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:23,500
the hydrogen was ionized at temperatures

74
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:25,620
higher than about 1,000,

75
00:03:25,660 --> 00:03:26,300
well,

76
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:29,200
about a few thousand degrees.

77
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:33,000
And so out beyond some place,

78
00:03:33,160 --> 00:03:36,220
