00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:20,660
So let's talk about what was out there.

167
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:22,100
Incidentally,

168
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:25,420
the particles in here,

169
00:07:25,540 --> 00:07:27,120
in addition to the photons,

170
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:31,140
are mainly protons and electrons.

171
00:07:32,219 --> 00:07:32,960
Now,

172
00:07:32,960 --> 00:07:36,280
protons mean the nuclei of hydrogen.

173
00:07:36,620 --> 00:07:39,140
There's also some helium nuclei,

174
00:07:39,640 --> 00:07:40,800
alpha particles,

175
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:42,640
and a few,

176
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:44,840
deuterons,

177
00:07:45,020 --> 00:07:47,980
which are an isotope of helium,

178
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:50,250
but basically just very simple elements like

179
00:07:50,250 --> 00:07:52,260
hydrogen and a little bit of helium.

180
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:54,360
As far as nuclei,

181
00:07:55,660 --> 00:07:57,460
electrons freely moving around.

182
00:07:58,180 --> 00:07:58,820
Now,

183
00:07:58,820 --> 00:08:00,520
no antiprotons,

184
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:01,480
no positrons,

185
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:03,920
or practically no antiprotons,

186
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:05,400
practically no positrons,

187
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:08,500
just ordinary matter,

188
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:09,580
pretty much.

189
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,680
Ordinary matter except ionized.

190
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:12,800
Now,

191
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:13,620
as we go out,

192
00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:17,800
we eventually come to a temperature

193
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:20,820
which is high enough

194
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:24,940
that when two photons collide,

195
00:08:28,660 --> 00:08:30,940
two photons collide.

196
00:08:31,340 --> 00:08:34,360
There's the wiggly lines represent photons.

197
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:36,580
The two photons collide.

198
00:08:37,539 --> 00:08:38,419
Normally,

199
00:08:38,419 --> 00:08:41,559
you think of photons as not things which collide,

200
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:42,700
you think of ordinary light,

201
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:44,140
light just passes through light,

202
00:08:44,380 --> 00:08:48,400
but high energy photons do collide with each other,

203
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:51,300
and basically what happens

204
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:54,080
is they create electron-positron pairs.

205
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:56,820
What comes out of here

206
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:59,880
could be two photons again.

207
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:00,720
In fact,

208
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:01,960
the photons might not even collide,

209
00:09:02,060 --> 00:09:03,360
they might just go right through each other,

210
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:06,080
but with some probability,

211
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:10,080
a probability of about one in 10,000

212
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:11,140
or something like that,

213
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:14,860
these photons can create an electron.

214
00:09:16,020 --> 00:09:17,520
Let's call it E minus.

215
00:09:17,620 --> 00:09:19,340
The minus stands for the fact

216
00:09:19,340 --> 00:09:21,060
that the electron has negative charge,

217
00:09:21,870 --> 00:09:23,180
and a positron,

218
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:27,760
which means the antiparticle of an electron.

219
00:09:28,260 --> 00:09:29,540
A positron,

220
00:09:29,540 --> 00:09:30,580
which we call E plus.

221
00:09:31,260 --> 00:09:33,740
Positrons and electrons are very,

222
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:35,240
very similar to each other.

223
00:09:35,980 --> 00:09:39,080
They are practically identical with one exception.

224
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,500
They have opposite charge.

225
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:44,440
They have the same mass,

226
00:09:44,620 --> 00:09:46,100
exactly the same mass,

227
00:09:47,380 --> 00:09:49,570
and properties which are almost

228
00:09:49,570 --> 00:09:51,760
direct reflections of each other.

229
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:52,860
For example,

230
00:09:52,860 --> 00:09:55,820
if you take two positrons,

231
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:57,630
they will behave exactly the same

232
00:09:57,630 --> 00:09:59,360
way as two electrons would behave,

233
00:09:59,540 --> 00:10:01,120
except with electrons being replaced

234
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,700
by positrons and so forth.

235
00:10:02,980 --> 00:10:04,020
Almost exactly,

236
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:04,920
not quite.

237
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:08,560
So if you go back far enough,

238
00:10:08,820 --> 00:10:09,660
now,

239
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:12,600
this will not happen with ordinary light,

240
00:10:12,740 --> 00:10:15,180
the light in this room,

241
00:10:15,460 --> 00:10:19,300
or the colliding light between the two bulbs up there.

242
00:10:19,820 --> 00:10:22,520
The reason is that the photons don't have enough energy.

243
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:25,680
The energy of these two electrons,

244
00:10:26,420 --> 00:10:29,380
even if the electrons were standing absolutely still,

245
00:10:30,119 --> 00:10:32,120
if they had no motion at all,

246
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:34,440
the energy would be twice,

247
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:36,560
two because there are two of them,

248
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:38,720
times the mass of the electron,

249
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:40,200
times the speed of light squared.

250
00:10:41,020 --> 00:10:41,620
Now,

251
00:10:41,620 --> 00:10:43,600
that's a significant amount of energy.

252
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:47,420
It's a lot more energy than photons,

253
00:10:47,560 --> 00:10:48,200
for example,

254
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:48,860
from the sun.

255
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:54,480
Two photons from the sun have energies much,

256
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:55,720
much less than that,

257
00:10:56,819 --> 00:10:59,100
thousands and thousands of times less than that.

258
00:10:59,220 --> 00:11:01,720
So two photons colliding,

259
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:02,880
for example,

260
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:05,160
from two different stars,

261
00:11:05,260 --> 00:11:08,060
will not have nearly enough energy to do that,

262
00:11:08,060 --> 00:11:09,940
but as the temperature goes up,

263
00:11:09,940 --> 00:11:13,140
as the universe gets more and more dense,

264
00:11:13,180 --> 00:11:14,620
going backward in time,

265
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:17,900
the photons become shorter and shorter wavelength,

266
00:11:18,380 --> 00:11:19,500
and eventually,

267
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:21,080
out somewheres,

268
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:22,480
or at some very early time,

269
00:11:22,780 --> 00:11:26,460
the universe was hot enough that photons,

270
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:27,980
when they collide,

271
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:29,780
make electron-positron pairs.

272
00:11:30,380 --> 00:11:32,440
Electron-positrons can collide with

273
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:34,500
each other and make photons.

274
00:11:34,900 --> 00:11:37,560
Exactly the inverse reaction can happen.

275
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:40,320
If you were to take a

276
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:43,080
pot of material at that temperature,

277
00:11:43,420 --> 00:11:46,680
you would have reactions similar to chemical reactions,

278
00:11:46,980 --> 00:11:49,640
except the chemicals now would be replaced by particles,

279
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:54,020
and the chem-nature of the chemical reactions would be

280
00:11:54,020 --> 00:11:57,320
photon pairs become electron-positron pairs,

281
00:11:57,560 --> 00:11:59,660
electron-positron pairs can collide.

282
00:11:59,880 --> 00:12:00,280
In fact,

283
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:02,430
this positron over here can collide

284
00:12:02,430 --> 00:12:04,580
with some other electron over here,

285
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:06,040
make more photons,

286
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:07,500
and eventually,

287
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:09,470
if the pot is allowed to just

288
00:12:09,470 --> 00:12:11,440
sit there for a long enough time,

289
00:12:11,740 --> 00:12:13,840
it will come to a thermal equilibrium.

290
00:12:14,780 --> 00:12:16,380
And in that thermal equilibrium,

291
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:19,470
there will be a certain ratio

292
00:12:19,470 --> 00:12:22,300
of photons to electrons and positrons.

293
00:12:22,760 --> 00:12:25,120
The number of electrons and positrons,

294
00:12:25,260 --> 00:12:26,280
you would think,

295
00:12:26,280 --> 00:12:27,480
if we really,

296
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:28,100
really started

297
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:32,400
with no electrons and positrons to begin with,

298
00:12:32,620 --> 00:12:34,520
now that's of course not accurate,

299
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:36,340
there are electrons in our universe,

300
00:12:36,580 --> 00:12:38,920
but in fact the electrons are very,

301
00:12:38,920 --> 00:12:41,080
very dilute compared with the photons.

302
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:44,220
There's approximately 10 to the 9th

303
00:12:44,220 --> 00:12:46,480
photons in the universe for every electron,

304
00:12:46,660 --> 00:12:47,780
so let's ignore the electrons

305
00:12:47,780 --> 00:12:48,900
which are there to begin with,

306
00:12:49,100 --> 00:12:50,540
but as we go backward,

307
00:12:51,260 --> 00:12:54,760
electrons get manufactured by this pair production process,

308
00:12:55,420 --> 00:12:57,740
and so that in the early universe,

309
00:12:58,460 --> 00:13:01,040
the only way they can be manufactured in this way

310
00:13:01,040 --> 00:13:02,700
is to manufacture both a positron

311
00:13:02,700 --> 00:13:04,360
and an electron at the same time,

312
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:06,650
so apart from this little bit of

313
00:13:06,650 --> 00:13:08,780
excess of electrons that's presently here now,

314
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:09,980
as we go backward,

315
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:12,740
we come to a time when the

316
00:13:12,740 --> 00:13:15,320
universe had equal amounts of electrons and positrons,

317
00:13:16,980 --> 00:13:20,340
or almost equal amounts of electrons and positrons,

318
00:13:22,140 --> 00:13:23,620
at some temperature.

319
00:13:26,560 --> 00:13:27,800
At first,

320
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:31,340
first means at temperatures which are not too high,

321
00:13:31,580 --> 00:13:34,460
there will be more photons than electrons,

322
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:35,440
and so we'll have electrons and positrons.

323
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:36,340
Why is that?

324
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:37,360
Well,

325
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:40,310
if we lower the temperature down below

326
00:13:40,310 --> 00:13:43,260
where the photons have enough energy for this,

327
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:45,300
there won't be any electrons and positrons.

328
00:13:46,140 --> 00:13:47,690
So it stands to reason if

329
00:13:47,690 --> 00:13:49,240
we raise the temperature a little bit,

330
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:51,690
just above the threshold for

331
00:13:51,690 --> 00:13:54,060
making a few electrons and positrons,

332
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:56,220
there will be mostly photons

333
00:13:56,220 --> 00:13:58,080
with a few electrons and positrons.

334
00:13:58,400 --> 00:14:00,280
But as the temperature heats up,

335
00:14:00,340 --> 00:14:01,740
and what this has to do with

336
00:14:02,340 --> 00:14:03,680
is the fact that the photons,

337
00:14:04,520 --> 00:14:06,900
the electrons have mass and the photons don't.

338
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:08,780
Photons have no mass,

339
00:14:08,780 --> 00:14:09,960
electrons have mass,

340
00:14:10,260 --> 00:14:13,980
electrons have some internal energy due to their mass,

341
00:14:14,100 --> 00:14:15,080
photons don't.

342
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:17,580
But as you heat it up higher and higher,

343
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:21,220
the kinetic energy of the electrons becomes much,

344
00:14:21,220 --> 00:14:23,460
much larger than their mc2 energy,

345
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:26,120
and the mc2 is not important.

346
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:29,220
So eventually when the temperature

347
00:14:29,220 --> 00:14:32,000
gets much above the threshold

348
00:14:32,319 --> 00:14:34,320
for creating electron-positron,

349
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:34,600
electron-positron pairs,

350
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:38,220
electrons and positrons,

351
00:14:38,340 --> 00:14:40,260
their mass is not important,

352
00:14:41,020 --> 00:14:42,860
the photons have no mass,

353
00:14:43,140 --> 00:14:43,760
electrons,

354
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:44,560
positrons,

355
00:14:44,560 --> 00:14:47,940
and photons become energetically very similar to each other,

356
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:50,060
and all of a sudden,

357
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:51,100
not all of a sudden,

358
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:52,880
but at that point,

359
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:56,080
the number of electrons and positrons,

360
00:14:56,140 --> 00:14:57,800
the density of them,

361
00:14:57,980 --> 00:15:00,520
is about the same as the number of photons,

362
00:15:01,439 --> 00:15:02,620
roughly speaking,

363
00:15:04,719 --> 00:15:05,439
electrons,

364
00:15:05,439 --> 00:15:06,160
photons,

365
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:09,180
and positrons all have the same density,

366
00:15:09,340 --> 00:15:11,500
and they're all colliding around like mad.

367
00:15:11,820 --> 00:15:13,080
This is a very,

368
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:16,620
very dense soup of charged particles.

369
00:15:16,940 --> 00:15:18,460
But what about the protons?

370
00:15:19,439 --> 00:15:22,060
The protons are still present.

371
00:15:22,780 --> 00:15:23,500
Incidentally,

372
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:28,060
they are rather dense by now.

373
00:15:31,380 --> 00:15:32,600
Millions of times more.

374
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:35,700
They're sometimes denser than they are in this room.

375
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:37,480
They're very dense,

376
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:38,180
the protons,

377
00:15:38,560 --> 00:15:42,600
but there is not yet enough thermal energy

378
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:46,820
to be able to create protons and antiprotons,

379
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:49,670
for either photons to collide

380
00:15:49,670 --> 00:15:52,420
and create protons and antiprotons,

381
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:54,800
or electrons and positrons to collide.

382
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:56,560
Why not?

383
00:15:56,860 --> 00:15:57,400
Well,

384
00:15:57,400 --> 00:16:00,600
it's because the energy of a proton

385
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:04,360
is m proton c squared,

386
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:08,300
and that's about 2,000 times larger

387
00:16:09,060 --> 00:16:11,660
than the energy of the mass of an electron.

388
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:13,800
The mass of a proton is

389
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:15,800
about 2,000 times larger than an electron.

390
00:16:16,020 --> 00:16:19,080
If you wanted to create a proton and an antiproton,

391
00:16:19,180 --> 00:16:21,460
you would need at least that much energy.

392
00:16:22,260 --> 00:16:22,780
So,

393
00:16:22,780 --> 00:16:24,020
as you go back,

394
00:16:24,140 --> 00:16:25,380
the universe contracts

395
00:16:25,380 --> 00:16:28,840
in the sense of going backward in time.

396
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:30,320
The universe contracts,

397
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:32,400
gets hotter and hotter and hotter,

398
00:16:32,660 --> 00:16:35,780
and eventually it rises to the threshold

399
00:16:37,150 --> 00:16:38,540
where it becomes hot enough

400
00:16:38,910 --> 00:16:43,360
that the particles can create proton-antiproton pairs.

401
00:16:46,130 --> 00:16:47,900
And so this dense soup

402
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:50,380
now becomes a soup of photons,

403
00:16:51,230 --> 00:16:51,660
electrons,

404
00:16:51,660 --> 00:16:53,080
positrons,

405
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:54,200
protons,

406
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:56,180
and antiprotons.

407
00:16:57,150 --> 00:16:57,580
But

408
00:16:58,980 --> 00:17:01,480
that's not really quite accurate.

409
00:17:01,940 --> 00:17:03,120
And the reason...

410
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:03,640
No,

411
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:04,420
it's not...

412
00:17:04,420 --> 00:17:06,160
It's more or less accurate.

413
00:17:06,359 --> 00:17:07,140
It's more or less accurate.

414
00:17:07,380 --> 00:17:08,000
Incidentally,

415
00:17:08,140 --> 00:17:11,700
the number of protons in the universe

416
00:17:11,700 --> 00:17:12,640
is about...

417
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:13,240
Not about.

418
00:17:13,520 --> 00:17:14,500
As far as we know,

419
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:16,760
it's the same as the number of electrons

420
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:18,680
because the universe is electrically neutral.

421
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:23,300
There's no net charge in the universe.

422
00:17:23,560 --> 00:17:25,660
So the universe is electrically neutral.

423
00:17:26,060 --> 00:17:27,560
And if it's electrically neutral,

424
00:17:27,560 --> 00:17:29,940
it must mean there's as many positively charged particles

425
00:17:29,940 --> 00:17:30,420
as negative.

426
00:17:30,860 --> 00:17:32,880
The only thing around today

427
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:34,800
are protons and electrons.

428
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:38,940
And so only charged particles around today

429
00:17:38,940 --> 00:17:39,860
are electrons and protons.

430
00:17:40,060 --> 00:17:40,760
So the number of electrons

431
00:17:40,760 --> 00:17:41,800
and the number of protons

432
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:42,960
is the same today.

433
00:17:43,740 --> 00:17:44,740
But of course,

434
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:47,240
once these positrons got into the act,

435
00:17:47,820 --> 00:17:50,380
there were a lot more electrons and positrons

436
00:17:50,380 --> 00:17:51,180
than there were protons.

437
00:17:51,820 --> 00:17:53,640
But now we keep heating it up.

438
00:17:53,700 --> 00:17:54,800
We keep heating it up.

439
00:17:55,260 --> 00:17:56,400
What happens

440
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:59,780
is not that we really create large numbers

441
00:17:59,780 --> 00:18:02,160
of protons and antiprotons,

442
00:18:02,260 --> 00:18:04,200
but very shortly,

443
00:18:04,340 --> 00:18:06,520
by the time we get to the energy needed

444
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:08,820
to create protons and antiprotons,

445
00:18:08,980 --> 00:18:10,520
there's also enough energy

446
00:18:10,520 --> 00:18:13,540
to smash the protons into quarks.

447
00:18:15,840 --> 00:18:20,300
And so by the time you get to the energy

448
00:18:20,300 --> 00:18:22,000
or the temperatures

449
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:25,600
where protons and antiprotons

450
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:29,440
become significant in this soup,

451
00:18:29,700 --> 00:18:33,280
really what you have is quarks.

452
00:18:33,700 --> 00:18:36,180
Three quarks for every proton.

453
00:18:36,780 --> 00:18:40,700
Three anti-quarks for every antiproton.

454
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:43,080
And basically the kind of reaction

455
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:44,460
that can take place,

456
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:47,460
I'll just draw you some simple diagrams

457
00:18:47,460 --> 00:18:49,800
that show you what kind of reactions

458
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:50,640
can take place.

459
00:18:51,660 --> 00:18:54,340
The simplest one is an electron

460
00:18:54,340 --> 00:18:56,160
and a positron come together,

461
00:18:56,420 --> 00:18:58,180
E plus and E minus.

462
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:02,180
They create a photon.

463
00:19:05,120 --> 00:19:09,600
That photon very quickly becomes something else.

464
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:13,740
It becomes a quark and an anti-quark,

465
00:19:13,760 --> 00:19:13,960
Q,

466
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:15,180
that stands for quark.

467
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:17,320
Could be a positively charged quark

468
00:19:17,320 --> 00:19:19,240
and a negatively charged quark.

469
00:19:19,740 --> 00:19:23,060
There are in fact several different kinds of quarks.

470
00:19:23,060 --> 00:19:25,440
There are quarks whose charges

471
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:28,340
are one third of the electron charge.

472
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:30,280
There are quarks whose charges are two thirds.

473
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:33,340
But I don't want now to get into the

474
00:19:33,340 --> 00:19:36,120
particle physics of quarks.

475
00:19:36,340 --> 00:19:38,860
The main thing is that

476
00:19:38,860 --> 00:19:41,340
the soup becomes a soup

477
00:19:41,340 --> 00:19:45,600
not only of electrons,

478
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:46,980
positrons,

479
00:19:46,980 --> 00:19:47,820
and protons.

480
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:51,640
The protons are replaced by quarks

481
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:56,240
and in addition lots and lots of anti-quarks.

482
00:19:57,060 --> 00:20:00,800
Almost as many anti-quarks as quarks.

483
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:03,780
And so if we go back far enough,

484
00:20:04,140 --> 00:20:05,120
Yeah?

485
00:20:05,540 --> 00:20:07,300
Is it mesons or pre-quarks?

486
00:20:08,020 --> 00:20:09,960
Mesons are made out of quarks.

487
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:12,740
Once the temperature gets high enough

488
00:20:12,740 --> 00:20:15,440
to shatter a proton,

489
00:20:15,720 --> 00:20:17,400
it also shatters the mesons.

490
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:20,760
Now there's one more constituent,

491
00:20:20,760 --> 00:20:23,060
there are other particles there too.

492
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:24,220
There are neutrinos

493
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:26,800
and all sorts of particles.

494
00:20:27,340 --> 00:20:28,620
Also gluons.

495
00:20:28,980 --> 00:20:29,920
What are gluons?

496
00:20:30,580 --> 00:20:32,660
Gluons are very much like photons

497
00:20:32,660 --> 00:20:35,720
but they're the things which are involved

498
00:20:35,720 --> 00:20:37,000
in holding quarks together.

499
00:20:37,360 --> 00:20:39,000
So there's all kinds of garbage.

500
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:43,640
It's a hot soup of all of the particles

501
00:20:43,640 --> 00:20:46,320
that we normally consider in atomic physics

502
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:47,580
and in nuclear physics.

503
00:20:48,540 --> 00:20:48,860
Okay?

504
00:20:49,780 --> 00:20:52,780
That's when the temperature gets to be hot enough

505
00:20:52,780 --> 00:20:59,120
for protons to be disassociated.

506
00:20:59,420 --> 00:21:02,540
If you ask me in degrees how hot that is,

507
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:03,800
I will have to think for a while.

508
00:21:06,420 --> 00:21:07,320
Ask me later.

509
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:08,560
We can work it out.

510
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:11,880
But at some temperature,

511
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:12,940
this begins to happen.

512
00:21:13,380 --> 00:21:13,820
Now,

513
00:21:13,820 --> 00:21:14,440
yeah?

514
00:21:14,700 --> 00:21:15,760
This would be hotter than,

515
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:16,100
say,

516
00:21:16,100 --> 00:21:16,820
inside a star.

517
00:21:17,180 --> 00:21:17,660
Yes,

518
00:21:17,660 --> 00:21:18,840
this is hotter than inside a star.

519
00:21:18,860 --> 00:21:19,280
Definitely.

520
00:21:20,040 --> 00:21:20,980
Inside a star,

521
00:21:22,780 --> 00:21:25,860
there are no anti-particles

522
00:21:26,780 --> 00:21:27,460
for the most part.

523
00:21:27,660 --> 00:21:27,840
Right?

524
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:30,660
So there aren't even positrons

525
00:21:30,660 --> 00:21:32,840
of any abundance inside stars.

526
00:21:33,140 --> 00:21:33,340
Yeah?

527
00:21:33,520 --> 00:21:35,280
So the sequence is going backwards in time,

528
00:21:35,280 --> 00:21:35,540
right?

529
00:21:35,660 --> 00:21:36,100
Yeah.

530
00:21:36,140 --> 00:21:38,660
So the real sequence is the other way around.

531
00:21:38,660 --> 00:21:38,740
Yeah,

532
00:21:38,740 --> 00:21:40,040
the real sequence is the other way around.

533
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:41,100
That's what I want to get to.

534
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:43,000
I want to get back to a starting point

535
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:46,520
and then discuss how it happened that...

536
00:21:47,300 --> 00:21:47,920
All right.

537
00:21:47,920 --> 00:21:52,020
So if you get things hot enough,

538
00:21:53,780 --> 00:21:57,060
there's going to be a huge density

539
00:21:57,060 --> 00:22:00,560
of particles and anti-particles.

540
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:03,600
The particles and the anti-particles

541
00:22:03,600 --> 00:22:05,540
will occur in pairs like this,

542
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:08,320
so there will be an equal abundance,

543
00:22:09,780 --> 00:22:12,340
almost essentially an equal abundance

544
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:16,440
of positrons and electrons on the one hand

545
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:17,900
and almost equal abundance

546
00:22:17,920 --> 00:22:19,640
of quarks and anti-quarks.

547
00:22:21,660 --> 00:22:22,280
In fact,

548
00:22:22,280 --> 00:22:24,880
if we go back sufficiently far,

549
00:22:29,679 --> 00:22:31,920
then the universe contains

550
00:22:32,920 --> 00:22:35,020
more or less equal abundances

551
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:36,860
of every kind of particle

552
00:22:36,860 --> 00:22:38,220
and its anti-particle.

553
00:22:38,980 --> 00:22:40,360
It starts out...

554
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:41,580
It's electrically neutral

555
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:44,980
because it's electrically neutral today.

556
00:22:45,020 --> 00:22:45,460
Incidentally,

557
00:22:45,460 --> 00:22:46,760
there's kind of an interesting reason

558
00:22:46,760 --> 00:22:48,360
why the universe is...

559
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:51,540
or a simple way of thinking about the fact

560
00:22:51,540 --> 00:22:53,320
that the universe is electrically neutral.

561
00:22:54,320 --> 00:22:57,660
If the universe is closed and bounded,

562
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:58,660
in other words,

563
00:22:58,660 --> 00:23:00,160
if it has the shape of a sphere,

564
00:23:00,280 --> 00:23:01,000
a three-sphere,

565
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:01,960
not a two-sphere,

566
00:23:02,640 --> 00:23:04,200
but if it has the shape of a sphere,

567
00:23:04,280 --> 00:23:05,460
just think about this for a moment.

568
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:08,640
Let's use as our model of the universe

569
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:11,360
a two-dimensional sphere,

570
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:12,360
the surface of a balloon.

571
00:23:13,240 --> 00:23:13,760
Now,

572
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:15,220
electrically charged particles

573
00:23:15,220 --> 00:23:17,900
put out lines of force.

574
00:23:18,020 --> 00:23:20,880
Those lines of force are the electric field.

575
00:23:21,300 --> 00:23:24,140
So if I put an electrically charged particle...

576
00:23:24,140 --> 00:23:25,580
Let's begin with flat space.

577
00:23:25,820 --> 00:23:26,480
Here's flat space.

578
00:23:27,840 --> 00:23:30,440
And let's put a positively charged particle in.

579
00:23:31,360 --> 00:23:32,960
Electric lines of force

580
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:35,560
go out away from that particle.

581
00:23:37,400 --> 00:23:39,560
And those electric lines of force

582
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:41,080
are simply the electric field

583
00:23:41,080 --> 00:23:42,720
or a way of representing...

584
00:23:44,460 --> 00:23:45,060
describing...

585
00:23:45,220 --> 00:23:47,600
or representing the electric field

586
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:48,680
of the charged particle.

587
00:23:50,480 --> 00:23:52,340
But it's useful graphically

588
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:55,480
to just think of it as lines of force.

589
00:23:55,740 --> 00:23:57,040
And the lines of force

590
00:23:57,040 --> 00:23:58,380
neither begin nor end

591
00:23:58,380 --> 00:24:00,040
except at charged particles.

592
00:24:01,540 --> 00:24:04,040
What law of physics is involved

593
00:24:04,040 --> 00:24:05,480
in saying the lines of force

594
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:07,880
never end except at charged particles?

595
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:09,240
Maxwell's equations.

596
00:24:10,300 --> 00:24:10,860
Well,

597
00:24:10,860 --> 00:24:11,940
it is Maxwell's equations,

598
00:24:12,120 --> 00:24:13,380
but it goes back a little...

599
00:24:13,380 --> 00:24:15,140
to something a little simpler than Maxwell's.

600
00:24:15,220 --> 00:24:16,480
It's the Coulomb force,

601
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:18,360
the one over r squared force law.

602
00:24:18,880 --> 00:24:20,940
The one over r squared force law

603
00:24:20,940 --> 00:24:23,880
is the rule that says that...

604
00:24:23,880 --> 00:24:25,520
is equivalent to the rule that says

605
00:24:25,520 --> 00:24:26,540
that the lines of force

606
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:29,460
never end except on charged particles.

607
00:24:31,660 --> 00:24:33,440
Positive charged particles

608
00:24:33,440 --> 00:24:34,820
put out lines of force.

609
00:24:34,940 --> 00:24:36,220
Negative charged particles

610
00:24:36,220 --> 00:24:38,680
suck in lines of force.

611
00:24:39,100 --> 00:24:39,700
Now,

612
00:24:39,700 --> 00:24:40,380
that's fine.

613
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:43,000
But supposing we lived in a world

614
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:44,940
which was this closed

615
00:24:45,220 --> 00:24:47,080
and bounded spherical world.

616
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:50,600
Supposing we put a charged particle into it.

617
00:24:51,260 --> 00:24:53,080
Let's put the charged particle over here.

618
00:24:53,980 --> 00:24:55,860
Then the lines of force go out,

619
00:24:57,620 --> 00:24:59,800
but they don't have anywhere to escape to.

620
00:25:01,820 --> 00:25:03,100
What happens to them?

621
00:25:04,300 --> 00:25:05,820
They just go around forever?

622
00:25:06,300 --> 00:25:06,820
Well,

623
00:25:06,820 --> 00:25:07,940
they don't move.

624
00:25:08,240 --> 00:25:08,480
I mean,

625
00:25:08,480 --> 00:25:09,200
they're...

626
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:11,180
They can't go around...

627
00:25:11,180 --> 00:25:12,060
No,

628
00:25:12,060 --> 00:25:12,860
they don't go around forever.

629
00:25:12,860 --> 00:25:14,860
They simply refocus

630
00:25:15,720 --> 00:25:17,120
on the other end of the sphere.

631
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:19,560
On the other pole.

632
00:25:19,720 --> 00:25:20,180
Supposing...

633
00:25:20,180 --> 00:25:21,000
For example,

634
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:21,940
supposing we put

635
00:25:21,940 --> 00:25:23,360
a positively charged particle

636
00:25:23,360 --> 00:25:25,000
at the north pole of the sphere.

637
00:25:25,500 --> 00:25:26,900
Turn this up so that it's

638
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:28,000
the north pole of the sphere.

639
00:25:28,660 --> 00:25:30,300
Then they simply refocus

640
00:25:30,300 --> 00:25:32,200
at the south pole of the sphere.

641
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:35,540
I don't know how to draw that.

642
00:25:35,960 --> 00:25:37,280
They refocus at the...

643
00:25:38,300 --> 00:25:39,900
at the other end of the sphere.

644
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:42,840
But refocusing on the other end

645
00:25:42,860 --> 00:25:45,120
means that the lines of flux,

646
00:25:45,380 --> 00:25:45,720
which...

647
00:25:45,720 --> 00:25:47,740
the lines of force which flow outward

648
00:25:47,740 --> 00:25:49,780
from the positive charge over here

649
00:25:52,740 --> 00:25:53,780
necessarily converge

650
00:25:57,520 --> 00:25:58,900
at the antipode.

651
00:26:00,300 --> 00:26:01,580
And what would that be

652
00:26:01,580 --> 00:26:03,280
if this were a positive charge?

653
00:26:03,660 --> 00:26:04,840
It would be a negative charge.

654
00:26:05,780 --> 00:26:07,900
So in a closed and bounded universe,

655
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:09,720
you can't have a net charge.

656
00:26:09,980 --> 00:26:10,820
So if you're saying

657
00:26:10,820 --> 00:26:12,500
that there was no negative charge there,

658
00:26:12,500 --> 00:26:13,560
there would be one there.

659
00:26:14,540 --> 00:26:16,140
If there was no negative charge there,

660
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:17,260
there would be that one there.

661
00:26:17,380 --> 00:26:17,600
Right.

662
00:26:18,780 --> 00:26:19,220
Right.

663
00:26:19,540 --> 00:26:22,240
It's just where the lines of flux converge.

664
00:26:22,580 --> 00:26:23,100
All right.

665
00:26:23,180 --> 00:26:23,700
But really,

666
00:26:23,700 --> 00:26:25,360
charged particles

667
00:26:25,360 --> 00:26:26,580
are charged particles.

668
00:26:26,780 --> 00:26:27,980
So you can ask what kind of

669
00:26:27,980 --> 00:26:29,420
charged particle would be there.

670
00:26:29,760 --> 00:26:31,720
The answer is any kind of particle

671
00:26:31,720 --> 00:26:32,680
with the opposite charge.

672
00:26:33,280 --> 00:26:34,760
So if this were a proton,

673
00:26:35,140 --> 00:26:36,780
this could be an antiproton

674
00:26:36,780 --> 00:26:37,720
or it could be an electron.

675
00:26:38,280 --> 00:26:42,400
The only rule is that every plus charge

676
00:26:42,500 --> 00:26:44,200
has to match,

677
00:26:44,260 --> 00:26:45,920
or the number of plus charges

678
00:26:45,920 --> 00:26:47,280
and the number of minus charges

679
00:26:47,280 --> 00:26:48,200
have to match.

680
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:49,520
In other words,

681
00:26:49,600 --> 00:26:51,720
in a closed and bounded universe,

682
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:56,220
the net charge must be zero.

683
00:26:57,040 --> 00:26:57,600
Now,

684
00:26:57,600 --> 00:26:58,440
it's not clear that we live

685
00:26:58,440 --> 00:26:59,680
