726
00:28:15,620 --> 00:28:17,960
is the same as the number of the opposite

727
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:20,120
of negatively charged particles.

728
00:28:20,940 --> 00:28:21,700
All right.

729
00:28:21,720 --> 00:28:23,420
So we started out with a universe

730
00:28:23,420 --> 00:28:24,360
with a very...

731
00:28:24,360 --> 00:28:25,080
We started out,

732
00:28:25,140 --> 00:28:27,060
or at least some time in the remote past,

733
00:28:27,360 --> 00:28:28,940
as far back as we can trace,

734
00:28:29,560 --> 00:28:31,640
using the known laws of physics

735
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:34,760
and maybe even going a little bit past

736
00:28:34,760 --> 00:28:35,960
the known laws of physics.

737
00:28:36,360 --> 00:28:37,920
We come to some stage

738
00:28:37,920 --> 00:28:40,480
where the universe was extremely hot,

739
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:42,320
how hot?

